# Cursor Repository Guardrails

## Canonical Layout

- `frontend/` – React + Vite app (TypeScript only, no `allowJs`)
- `src-tauri/` – Rust shell, migrations, assets (no `target/` or packaged binaries committed)
- `docs/` – All documentation (product, tech, process, testing, tickets)
- `tools/` – Scripts and helper utilities (`tools/scripts/*` for shell/Node helpers)
- `labs/` – Archived experiments or research references only

Root-level markdown is limited to `README.md`, `RUN_APP.md`, and `TESTING_GUIDE.md`.

## Allowed Content

- Frontend code must be `.ts`/`.tsx`. Delete any generated `.js` artifacts.
- Tauri backend uses SQLite by default; other database configs require approval and documentation in `docs/process/`.
- Tickets live under `docs/tickets/` and use `ticket-<slug>.md` filenames.
- Experiments, automation agents, and exploratory write-ups move to `labs/` (or are deleted).

## Off-Limits Without Approval

- Reintroducing the Python `intelligence-agent` microservice.
- Adding Docker Compose stacks, Grafana, Prometheus, or other infra directories.
- Checking in build outputs (`node_modules`, `dist`, `target`, `*.db`, logs).
- Creating new top-level folders or scattering docs outside `docs/`.

## Contributor Expectations

- Follow `docs/process/repo-structure.md` when adding files or folders.
- Place new scripts in `tools/scripts/` and document usage if needed.
- Keep documentation organized under `docs/` using kebab-case filenames.
- When in doubt, ask before expanding the scope beyond the desktop Tauri app + React frontend.

